<section name="Summary">

<p>
dishevelled.org <b>piccolo-transition</b> provides transitions [<a href="#1">1</a>]
implemented as Piccolo2D [<a href="#2">2</a>] activities.  The API attempts to follow the
Synchronized Multimedia Integration Language (SMIL) specification [<a href="#3">3</a>]
where appropriate.  The piccolo-transition library requires java version 1.6 or later.
</p>
</section>

<section name="References">
<p id="1">
[1] Yahoo! Design Pattern Library:  Transition<br/>
&gt; <a href="http://developer.yahoo.com/ypatterns/parent.php?pattern=transition">http://developer.yahoo.com/ypatterns/parent.php?pattern=transition</a>
</p>
<p id="2">
[2] Piccolo2D Toolkit<br/>
&gt; <a href="http://piccolo2d.org">http://piccolo2d.org</a>
</p>
<p id="3">
[3] Synchronized Multimedia Integration Language (SMIL 3.0)<br/>
&gt; <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/SMIL3/">http://www.w3.org/TR/SMIL3/</a>
</p>
</section>

